  "prompt": "Is there a way to tell if someone in Skype is currently in a call or messaging someone?",
  "response": "Yes, in Skype, you can see if someone is currently in a call or busy using certain indicators:\n\n1. **Status Indicators**: Skype uses status icons to show whether a user is available, busy, offline, or in a call. A green circle indicates they are available, while a red circle with a white phone icon means they are currently on a call. If their status is set to \"Do Not Disturb,\" it will also appear as a red circle, but without the phone icon.\n\n2. **Profile Information**: If you open someone's profile, you may see additional information about their status or activity.\n\n3. **Messaging Response**: If you send a message and it is marked as \"delivered\" but not seen, it could indicate that the person is currently busy or on a call.\n\nKeep in mind that users can manually set their status, so it's not always a guarantee that they are unavailable based on the status indicators alone.",
